<p>
Indicates the beginning of a quotation (a sumti) which is grammatical as long as the quoted material consists of Lojban words, whether they form a text or not. Terminated by LEhU.
<p>
<p>
<pre>do cusku lo'u mi du do du ko'a le'u
	You express [quote] mi du do du ko'a [end quote].
	You said, "mi du do du ko'a”.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "LU: selma'o catalog"> XE "LU: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "quotation: grammatical: selma'o catalog"> XE "quotation: grammatical: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o LU (<a href=chap19.html>Chapter 19</a>)
<p>
<p>
Indicates the beginning of a quotation (a sumti) which is grammatical only if the quoted material also forms a grammatical Lojban text. Terminated by LIhU.
<p>
<p>
<pre>mi cusku lu mi klama le zarci li'u
	I express [quote] I go-to the market [end quote].
</pre>
<p>
<lx "LUhU: selma'o catalog"> XE "LUhU: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "LAhE selma'o: terminator for: selma'o catalog"> XE "LAhE selma'o: terminator for: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "NAhE+BO: terminator for: selma'o catalog"> XE "NAhE+BO: terminator for: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o LUhU (<a href=chap6.html>Chapter 6</a>)
<p>
<p>
Elidable terminator for and . Indicates the end of a qualified sumti.
<p>
<p>
<pre>mi viska la'e lu barda gerku li'u lu'u
	I see the-referent-of [quote] big dog [end quote] [end ref]
	I saw "Big Dog” [not the words, but a book or movie].

</pre>
<p>
<lx "MAI: selma'o catalog"> XE "MAI: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "index numbering: selma'o catalog"> XE "index numbering: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o MAI (<a href=chap18.html>Chapter 18</a>, <a href=chap19.html>Chapter 19</a>)
<p>
<p>
When suffixed to a number or string of letter words, produces a free modifier which serves as an index number within a text.
<p>
<p>
<pre>pamai mi pu klama le zarci
	1-thly, I [past] go to-the market.
	First, I went to the market.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "MAhO: selma'o catalog"> XE "MAhO: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "converting: operand to operator: selma'o catalog"> XE "converting: operand to operator: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o MAhO (<a href=chap18.html>Chapter 18</a>)
<p>
<p>
Produces a mathematical operator from a letter or other operand. Terminated by . See .
<p>
<p>
<pre>ma'o fy. boi xy.
	[operator] f x
	f(x)
</pre>
<p>
<lx "ME: selma'o catalog"> XE "ME: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "converting: sumti to tanru unit: selma'o catalog"> XE "converting: sumti to tanru unit: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o ME (<a href=chap5.html>Chapter 5</a>, <a href=chap18.html>Chapter 18</a>)
<p>
<p>
Produces a tanru unit from a sumti, which is applicable to the things referenced by the sumti. Terminated by MEhU.
<p>
<p>
<pre>ta me la ford. karce
	That is-a-Ford-type car.
	That's a Ford car.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "MEhU: selma'o catalog"> XE "MEhU: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "ME selma'o: terminator for: selma'o catalog"> XE "ME selma'o: terminator for: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o MEhU (<a href=chap5.html>Chapter 5</a>)
<p>
<p>
The elidable terminator for ME. Indicates the end of a sumti converted to a tanru unit.
<p>
<p>
<pre>ta me mi me'u zdani
	That's a me type of house.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "MOI: selma'o catalog"> XE "MOI: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "converting: quantifier to selbri: selma'o catalog"> XE "converting: quantifier to selbri: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o MOI (<a href=chap5.html>Chapter 5</a>, )
<p>
<p>
Suffixes added to numbers or other quantifiers to make various numerically-based selbri.
<p>
<p>
<pre>la djan. joi la frank. cu bruna remei
	John in-a-mass-with Frank are-a-brother-type-of twosome.
	John and Frank are two brothers.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "MOhE: selma'o catalog"> XE "MOhE: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "converting: sumti to operand: selma'o catalog"> XE "converting: sumti to operand: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o MOhE (<a href=chap18.html>Chapter 18</a>)
<p>
<p>
Produces a mathematical operand from a sumti; used to make dimensioned units. Terminated by TEhU.
<p>
<p>
<pre>li mo'e re ratcu su'i mo'e re ractu du li mo'e vo danlu
The-number two rats plus two rabbits equals the-number four animals.
	2 rats + 2 rabbits = 4 animals.

</pre>
<p>
<lx "MOhI: selma'o catalog"> XE "MOhI: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "space movement indicator: selma'o catalog"> XE "space movement indicator: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o MOhI (<a href=chap10.html>Chapter 10</a>)
<p>
<p>
A tense flag indicating movement in space, in a direction specified by a following FAhA cmavo.
<p>
<p>
<pre>le verba mo'i ri'u cadzu le bisli
	The child [movement] [right] walks-on the ice.
	The child walks toward my right on the ice.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "NA: selma'o catalog"> XE "NA: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "negator: contradictory: selma'o catalog"> XE "negator: contradictory: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NA (<a href=chap14.html>Chapter 14</a>, <a href=chap15.html>Chapter 15</a>)
<p>
<p>
Contradictory negators, asserting that a whole bridi is false (or true).
<p>
<p>
<pre>mi na klama le zarci
	It is not true that I go to the market.
</pre>
<p><p>Also used to construct logical connective compound cmavo.
<p>

<lx "NAI: selma'o catalog"> XE "NAI: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "negator: single-word: selma'o catalog"> XE "negator: single-word: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NAI (<a href=chap14.html>Chapter 14</a>, <a href=chap15.html>Chapter 15</a>)
<p>
<p>
Negates the previous word, but can only be used with certain selma'o as specified by the grammar.
<p>

<lx "NAhE: selma'o catalog"> XE "NAhE: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "negator: scalar: selma'o catalog"> XE "negator: scalar: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NAhE (<a href=chap15.html>Chapter 15</a>)
<p>
<p>
Scalar negators, modifying a selbri or a sumti to a value other than the one stated, the opposite of the one stated, etc. Also used with following BO to construct a sumti qualifier; see LAhE.
<p>
<p>
<pre>ta na'e blanu zdani
	That is-a-non- blue house.
	That is a house which is other than blue.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "NAhU: selma'o catalog"> XE "NAhU: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "converting: selbri to operator: selma'o catalog"> XE "converting: selbri to operator: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NAhU (<a href=chap18.html>Chapter 18</a>)
<p>
<p>
Creates a mathematical operator from a selbri. Terminated by . See .
<p>
<p>
<pre>li na'u tanjo te'u vei pai fe'i re [ve'o] du li ci'i
	The-number the-operator tangent ((pi / 2 ) = the-number infinity.
	tan((pi/2) = infinity(
</pre>
<p>
<lx "NIhE: selma'o catalog"> XE "NIhE: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "converting: selbri to operand: selma'o catalog"> XE "converting: selbri to operand: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NIhE (<a href=chap18.html>Chapter 18</a>)
<p>
<p>
Creates a mathematical operand from a selbri, usually a "ni” abstraction. Terminated by TEhU. 
<p>
<p>
<pre>li ni'e ni clani [te'u] pi'i ni'e ni ganra [te'u] pi'i
		ni'e ni condi te'u du li ni'e ni canlu
	The-number quantity-of length times quantity-of width times
		quantity-of depth equals the-number quantity-of volume.
	Length ( Width ( Depth = Volume

</pre>
<p>
<lx "NIhO: selma'o catalog"> XE "NIhO: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "paragraph marker: selma'o catalog"> XE "paragraph marker: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NIhO (<a href=chap19.html>Chapter 19</a>)
<p>
<p>
Marks the beginning of a new paragraph, and indicates whether it contains old or new subject matter.
<p>

<lx "NOI: selma'o catalog"> XE "NOI: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "relative clause marker: selma'o catalog"> XE "relative clause marker: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NOI (<a href=chap8.html>Chapter 8</a>)
<p>
Introduces relative clauses. The following bridi modifies the preceding sumti. Terminated by . See .
 <p>
<pre>le zdani poi blanu cu cmalu
	The house which is blue is small.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "NU: selma'o catalog"> XE "NU: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "abstractors: selma'o catalog"> XE "abstractors: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NU (<a href=chap11.html>Chapter 11</a>)
<p>
<p>
Abstractors which, when prefixed to a bridi, create abstraction selbri. Terminated by .
<p>
<p>
<pre>la djan. cu djica le nu sonci [kei]
	John desires the event-of being-a-soldier.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "NUhA: selma'o catalog"> XE "NUhA: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "converting: operator to selbri: selma'o catalog"> XE "converting: operator to selbri: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NUhA (<a href=chap18.html>Chapter 18</a>)
<p>
<p>
Creates a selbri from a mathematical operator. See .
<p>
<p>
<pre>li ni'umu cu nu'a va'a li ma'umu
	The-number -5 is-the-negation-of the-number +5.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "NUhI: selma'o catalog"> XE "NUhI: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "termset marker: selma'o catalog"> XE "termset marker: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NUhI (<a href=chap14.html>Chapter 14</a>, <a href=chap16.html>Chapter 16</a>)
<p>
<p>
Marks the beginning of a termset, which is used to make simultaneous claims involving two or more different places of a selbri. Terminated by .
<p>
<p>
<pre>mi klama nu'i ge le zarci le briju nu'u gi le zdani
		le ckule [nu'u]
	I go [start] to-the market from-the office [joint] and to-the house
		from-the school.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "NUhU: selma'o catalog"> XE "NUhU: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "NUhU selma'o: terminator for: selma'o catalog"> XE "NUhU selma'o: terminator for: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o NUhU (<a href=chap14.html>Chapter 14</a>)
<p>
<p>
Elidable terminator for . Marks the end of a termset.
<p>
<p>
<pre> mi klama nu'i ge le zarci le briju nu'u gi le zdani
		le ckule [nu'u]
	I go [start] to-the market from-the office [joint] and to-the house
		from-the school.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "PA: selma'o catalog"> XE "PA: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "quantifiers: selma'o catalog"> XE "quantifiers: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "digits: selma'o catalog"> XE "digits: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o PA (<a href=chap18.html>Chapter 18</a>)
<p>
<p>
Digits and related quantifiers (some, all, many, etc.). Terminated by .
<p>
<p>
<pre>mi speni re ninmu
	I am-married-to two women.

</pre>
<p>
<lx "PEhE: selma'o catalog"> XE "PEhE: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "termset connectives: selma'o catalog"> XE "termset connectives: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o PEhE (<a href=chap14.html>Chapter 14</a>)
<p>
<p>
Precedes a logical or non-logical connective that joins two termsets. Termsets (see ) are used to associate several terms for logical connectives, for equal quantifier scope, or for special constructs in tenses.
<p>
<p>
<pre>mi ce'e do pe'e je la djan. ce'e la djeimyz. cu pendo
	I [,] you [joint] and John [,] James are-friends-of.
	I am a friend of you, and John is a friend of James.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "PEhO: selma'o catalog"> XE "PEhO: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "operator: forethought marker: selma'o catalog"> XE "operator: forethought marker: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o PEhO (<a href=chap18.html>Chapter 18</a>)
<p>
<p>
An optional signal of forethought mathematical operators, which precede their operands. Terminated by .
<p>
<p>
<pre>li vo du li pe'o su'i reboi re
	The-number four equals the-number [forethought] sum-of two two.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "PU: selma'o catalog"> XE "PU: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "direction: time: selma'o catalog"> XE "direction: time: selma'o catalog"
