Converts a selbri, rearranging the order of places by exchanging the x1 place with a specified numbered place.
<p>
<p>
<pre>le zarci se klama mi
	The market is-gone-to by me.
</pre>
<p><p>Also used in constructing connective and modal compound cmavo.
<p>

<lx "SEI: selma'o catalog"> XE "SEI: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "metalinguistic insertions: marker for: selma'o catalog"> XE "metalinguistic insertions: marker for: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o SEI (<a href=chap19.html>Chapter 19</a>)
<p>
<p>
Marks the beginning of metalinguistic insertions which comment on the main bridi. Terminated by .
<p>
<p>
<pre>la frank. prami sei gleki [se'u] la djein.
	Frank loves (he is happy) Jane.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "SEhU: selma'o catalog"> XE "SEhU: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "SEI selma'o: terminator for: selma'o catalog"> XE "SEI selma'o: terminator for: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "SOI selma'o: terminator for: selma'o catalog"> XE "SOI selma'o: terminator for: selma'o catalog"
   selma'o SEhU (<a href=chap19.html>Chapter 19</a>)
<p>
<p>
Elidable terminator for and . Ends metalinguistic insertions.
<p>
<p>
<pre>la frank. prami sei gleki se'u la djein.
	Frank loves (he is happy) Jane.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "SI: selma'o catalog"> XE "SI: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "erasing: word, selma'o catalog"> XE "erasing: word, selma'o catalog"
   selma'o SI (<a href=chap19.html>Chapter 19</a>)
<p>
<p>
Erases the previous single word.
<p>
<p>
<pre>mi si do klama le zarci
	I, er, you go to-the market.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "SOI: selma'o catalog"> XE "SOI: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "reciprocity: marking, selma'o catalog"> XE "reciprocity: marking, selma'o catalog"
   selma'o SOI (<a href=chap7.html>Chapter 7</a>)
<p>
<p>
Marks reciprocity between two sumti (like "vice versa” in English).
<p>
<p>
<pre>mi prami do soi mi
	I love you [reciprocally] me.
	I love you and vice versa.
</pre>
<p>
<lx "SU: selma'o catalog"> XE "SU: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "erasing: discourse, selma'o catalog"> XE "erasing: discourse, selma'o catalog"
   selma'o SU (<a href=chap19.html>Chapter 19</a>)
<p>
<p>
Closes and erases the entire previous discourse.
<p>

<lx "TAhE: selma'o catalog"> XE "TAhE: selma'o catalog"
   
<cx "frequency within interval: specifying, selma'o catalog"> XE "frequency within interval: specifying, selma'o catalog"
   selma'o TAhE (<a href=chap10.html>Chapter 10</a>)
<p>
<p>
A tense modifier specifying frequencies within an interval of time or space (regularly, habitually, etc.).
<p>
<p>
<pre>le verba ta'e klama le ckule
	The child habitually goes to-the school.

</pre>
